.TH "fsl_ssi_config_enable" 9 "fsl_ssi_config_enable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_ssi_config_enable \- Set SCR, SIER, STCR and SRCR registers with cached values in regvals
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fsl_ssi_config_enable
.BI "(struct fsl_ssi *ssi "  ","
.BI "bool tx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ssi" 12
SSI context
.IP "tx" 12
direction
.SH "NOTES"
1) For offline_config SoCs, enable all necessary bits of both streams
when 1st stream starts, even if the opposite stream will not start
2) It also clears FIFO before setting regvals; SOR is safe to set online
